South Africa Wants the U.S. to Honor Debt Committments it Made to Sudan

-- B y   C a r l i   L o u r e n s
-- 
2011-05-31T10:44:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/south-africa-wants-the-u-s-to-honor-debt-committments-it-made-to-sudan.html
(Corrects country name in headline and story.)  The U.S. should honor
commitments it made to  Sudan  and cancel the country’s debt
and remove the nation from its terrorism list, Maite Nkoana-Mashabane,  South Africa ’s Minister of International
Relations and Cooperation, told lawmakers in  Cape Town 
today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
